	(72,'news',1,1,0,'airpapr-is-now-boarding','cat_name_show_en','cat_description_en','airpapr-is-now-boarding','airpapr is now boarding!','24.12.10','Patrick','airpapr is now boarding!','<p>airpapr has been in development for two years now, and now, on the 24<sup>th</sup> of December 2010, airpapr finally gets a home on the world wide web. The development of airpapr began out of the necessity that we needed a flexible and powerful content management system, which at the same time is easy to use and lightweight. What started as small project for a single website soon became independent project which was used for multiple websites.</p>\r\n<p>Over the years airpapr has emerged into a full-featured content management system and the only logic step now for us was to release airpapr as open source software as soon as possible, so that everyone can use it freely and take part in development of airpapr. We plan to release the first public beta of airpapr as open source software in the near future. If you want more information on that airpapr is and how it works, have a look at the <a href=\\\"en/page/about-airpapr\\\">about page</a>.</p>','<p>airpapr has been in development for two years now, and now, on the 24<sup>th</sup> of December 2010, airpapr finally gets a home on the world wide web. The development of airpapr began out of the necessity that we needed a flexible and powerful content management system, which at the same time is easy to use and lightweight. What started as small project for a single website soon became independent project which was used for multiple websites.</p>\n\n<p><p>Over the years airpapr has emerged into a full-featured content management system and the only logic step now for us was to release airpapr as open source software as soon as possible, so that everyone can use it freely and take part in development of airpapr. We plan to release the first public beta of airpapr as open source software in the near future. If you want more information on that airpapr is and how it works, have a look at the <a href=\\\"en/page/about-airpapr\\\">about page</a>.</p></p>\n','','','airpapr-is-now-boarding-0.jpg','','',1),
	(74,'news',1,1,0,'php-5-oop-and-pdo','cat_name_show_en','cat_description_en','php-5-oop-and-pdo','PHP 5, OOP and PDO','15.01.11','Patrick','PHP 5, OOP and PDO','<p>Since the launch of the airpapr development blog, a lot as happened in the development of airpapr. First of all we started to switch the airpapr database connection driver form the old mysql database extensions to PHP\\\'s new <a href=\\\"http://www.php.net/manual/en/intro.pdo.php\\\">PHP Data Objects (PDO)</a> database abstraction layer. This means you don\\\'t have (but of curse you still can) use MySQL with airpapr any more. Now airpapr supports a wide variety of database, from SQLite over Microsoft SQL Server to PostgreSQL, <a href=\\\"http://www.phpro.org/tutorials/Introduction-to-PHP-PDO.html#2\\\">among others</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Also we are on the way of turning a lot of airpapr\\\'s functions, that are still writen in sequential PHP into object orient PHP, which will make airpapr faster, safer, and also easy to develop and improve onece airpapr is released.</p>\r\n<p>All these advances come at a small cost. If you have read through the airpapr about page (and if you haven\\\'t, I highly encourage you to <a href=\\\"/en/page/about-airpapr\\\">check it out</a>), you\\\'ll may have noticed the point that airpapr only needs PHP 4.1 work. This is not quite right any more, PHP Data Objects (PDO) database driver <a href=\\\"http://www.php.net/manual/en/intro.pdo.php\\\">requires PHP 5.1</a> to work. We decided to drop PHP 4 support, the possibilities which PHP 5 offer are more than worth the sacrifice of PHP 4 support, especially because nearly all webhosters offer PHP 5 on there servers nowadays, so our promise that airpapr is able to &ldquo;run on (nearly) any web hosting server.&rdquo; is still true!</p>','<p>Since the launch of the airpapr development blog, a lot as happened in the development of airpapr. First of all we started to switch the airpapr database connection driver form the old mysql database extensions to PHP\\\'s new <a href=\\\"http://www.php.net/manual/en/intro.pdo.php\\\">PHP Data Objects (PDO)</a> database abstraction layer. This means you don\\\'t have (but of curse you still can) use MySQL with airpapr any more. Now airpapr supports a wide variety of database, from SQLite over Microsoft SQL Server to PostgreSQL, <a href=\\\"http://www.phpro.org/tutorials/Introduction-to-PHP-PDO.html#2\\\">among others</a>.</p>\n\n<p><p>Also we are on the way of turning a lot of airpapr&#92;\'s functions, that are still writen in sequential PHP into object orient PHP, which will make airpapr faster, safer, and also easy to develop and improve onece airpapr is released.</p>\n<p>All these advances come at a small cost. If you have read through the airpapr about page (and if you haven&#92;\'t, I highly encourage you to <a href=\\\"/en/page/about-airpapr\\\">check it out</a>), you&#92;\'ll may have noticed the point that airpapr only needs PHP 4.1 work. This is not quite right any more, PHP Data Objects (PDO) database driver <a href=\\\"http://www.php.net/manual/en/intro.pdo.php\\\">requires PHP 5.1</a> to work. We decided to drop PHP 4 support, the possibilities which PHP 5 offer are more than worth the sacrifice of PHP 4 support, especially because nearly all webhosters offer PHP 5 on there servers nowadays, so our promise that airpapr is able to &ldquo;run on (nearly) any web hosting server.&rdquo; is still true!</p></p>\n','','','php-5-oop-and-pdo-0.png','','',1),
