	(80,'',2,2,0,'documentation','cat_name_show_en','cat_description_en','documentation','documentation','25.04.11','Patrick','documentation','<p>The airpapr documentation can be found on our&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/\\\">github page</a>.</p>\r\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/issues\\\">Known Bugs</a></em></p>\r\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/Changelog\\\">Changelog</a></em></p>\r\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/Features-to-come\\\">Features to come</a></em></p>\r\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/Template-API-Reference\\\">Template API refrence</a></em></p>\r\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/Template-file-structure\\\">Template file structure</a></em></p>','<p>The airpapr documentation can be found on our&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/\\\">github page</a>.</p>\n\n<p><p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/issues\\\">Known Bugs</a></em></p>\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/Changelog\\\">Changelog</a></em></p>\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/Features-to-come\\\">Features to come</a></em></p>\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/Template-API-Reference\\\">Template API refrence</a></em></p>\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/wiki/Template-file-structure\\\">Template file structure</a></em></p></p>\n','','','','','',1),
	(84,'news',1,1,0,'airpapr-update-step-by-step-installation','cat_name_show_en','cat_description_en','airpapr-update-step-by-step-installation','airpapr update: Step-by-step installation','13.06.11','Patrick','airpapr update: Step-by-step installation','<p>airpapr now has a step-by-step installation process. The installation process is automatically launched as soon as you have uploaded airpapr to your server. It will guide you through the initial setup of airpapr, help you set up the database and adding administrator accounts so you can start adding content to a default template.</p>\r\n<p>The database connection information you enter during the installation are stored under config&nbsp;<span style=\\\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; font-family: sans-serif;\\\">&rarr;</span>&nbsp;settings.inc.php. If you want to move your current installation of airpapr to an other database, you only need to delete the settings.inc.php file and the setup will automatically start again as soon as you visit your airpapr website again.You should not delete the settings.inc.php file while the website is live. If you delete the settings file on a live site, the next user visiting the site will see the setup process (it is generally not a good idea to change the database on a running site). Alternatively, you can also just edit the values in the settings.inc.php file to match your new database setup.</p>\r\n<p>All other settings you enter during the installation can be changed in the general settings menu of airpapr.</p>\r\n<p>If you have any problems during the installation, or want to give us a feedback, pleas contact us via <a href=\\\"//twitter.com/airpapr\\\">twitter</a> (@airpapr), on <a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/issues?sort=created&amp;direction=desc&amp;state=open\\\">github</a> or <a href=\\\"/en/contact\\\">email</a>!</p>','<p>airpapr now has a step-by-step installation process. The installation process is automatically launched as soon as you have uploaded airpapr to your server. It will guide you through the initial setup of airpapr, help you set up the database and adding administrator accounts so you can start adding content to a default template.</p>\n\n<p><p>The database connection information you enter during the installation are stored under config&nbsp;<span style=\\\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; font-family: sans-serif;\\\">&rarr;</span>&nbsp;settings.inc.php. If you want to move your current installation of airpapr to an other database, you only need to delete the settings.inc.php file and the setup will automatically start again as soon as you visit your airpapr website again.You should not delete the settings.inc.php file while the website is live. If you delete the settings file on a live site, the next user visiting the site will see the setup process (it is generally not a good idea to change the database on a running site). Alternatively, you can also just edit the values in the settings.inc.php file to match your new database setup.</p>\n<p>All other settings you enter during the installation can be changed in the general settings menu of airpapr.</p>\n<p>If you have any problems during the installation, or want to give us a feedback, pleas contact us via <a href=\\\"//twitter.com/airpapr\\\">twitter</a> (@airpapr), on <a href=\\\"https://github.com/airpapr/airpapr/issues?sort=created&amp;direction=desc&amp;state=open\\\">github</a> or <a href=\\\"/en/contact\\\">email</a>!</p></p>\n','','','airpapr-update-step-by-step-installation-0.png','','',1),
