	(85,'news',1,1,0,'the-webapp-development-stack-tools-that-will-make-your-life-easier','cat_name_show_en','cat_description_en','the-webapp-development-stack-tools-that-will-make-your-life-easier','The Webapp development stack - Tools that will make your life easier','1337065025','Patrick','The Webapp development stack - Tools that will make your life easier','<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Last night I was visiting Paul Irishs blog and had a look at his excellent talk at jQuery UK 2012, TOOLING &amp; THE WEBAPP DEVELOPMENT STACK. It\\\'s an excellent &amp; fun talk and you should defiantly have a look at it. Paul talks about different Tools for frontend developers that can make you a lot esyer. Paul lists a ton of useful tools, and I tried to create a list of all of the tools he mentions as a nice, compact summary:</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Boilerplates</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">The HTML 5 Boilerplate, a good point to start on any HTML document</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://html5boilerplate.com/\\\">http://html5boilerplate.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">blueprint - the first css boilerplate, there a lot, lot more but you can\\\'t go wrong with blueprint</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://blueprintcss.org/\\\">http://blueprintcss.org/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Think IE 6 is hell? Try writing HTML in E-Mails. Luckly there are boilerplates too</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://htmlemailboilerplate.com/\\\">http://htmlemailboilerplate.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">The HTML 5 Boilerplate from the beginning, only optimized for mobile. Yay!</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://html5boilerplate.com/mobile\\\">http://html5boilerplate.com/mobile</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Writing Dojo? There\\\'s a boilerplate for it too, so you don\\\'t have to figure out the best practice</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://github.com/csnover/dojo-boilerplate\\\">https://github.com/csnover/dojo-boilerplate</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Or are you writing jQuery? Then there is a boilerplate for you, too!</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://jqueryboilerplate.com/\\\">http://jqueryboilerplate.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Styling</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Writing CSS can be a pain. SASS makes it easy again, with support of nested rules, variables, selector inheritance and more. Compiles down to normal, valid CSS 3</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://sass-lang.com/\\\">http://sass-lang.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Lala&nbsp; - need to have a look at this one myself</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://compass-style.org/\\\">http://compass-style.org/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Alternative to SASS, introduces variables, functions and nested rules to CSS</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://lesscss.org/\\\">http://lesscss.org/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Another SASS alternative, also introduces variables, functions conditionals mixings to CSS</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://code.google.com/p/closure-stylesheets/\\\">http://code.google.com/p/closure-stylesheets/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Sylus - also a SASS alternative</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://learnboost.github.com/stylus/\\\">http://learnboost.github.com/stylus/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Markup</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Haml. - A what ever for ruby. Looks nice</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://haml.info/\\\">http://haml.info/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Mardown - a simple Markuplanguage, used at github and stack overflow. also works in airpapr ;)</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/\\\">http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">A template engine for node.js - makes your HTML much simpler</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://jade-lang.com/\\\">http://jade-lang.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">DAFUQ</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://handlebarsjs.com/\\\">http://handlebarsjs.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Awesome tool to write html as fast as hell - really great</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://code.google.com/p/zen-coding/\\\">http://code.google.com/p/zen-coding/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Scripting</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">A list of languages that compile to JavaScript</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://github.com/jashkenas/coffee-script/wiki/List-of-languages-that-compile-to-JS\\\">https://github.com/jashkenas/coffee-script/wiki/List-of-languages-that-compile-to-JS</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">CoffeScript - a language that compiles directly to JavaScript - easy to use</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://coffeescript.org/\\\">http://coffeescript.org/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Googls DART programming language - also compiles directly to JavaScript</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://www.dartlang.org/\\\">http://www.dartlang.org/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>ToDoMVC</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">The Same ToDo app implemented in various different JavaScriptMV* frameworks - great if you want to compare different frameworks and see which one is best for you</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://addyosmani.github.com/todomvc/\\\">http://addyosmani.github.com/todomvc/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Tools</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://livereload.com/\\\">http://livereload.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://incident57.com/codekit/\\\">http://incident57.com/codekit/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Editors</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://aptana.com/products/studio3\\\">http://aptana.com/products/studio3</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm/features/\\\">http://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm/features/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://net.tutsplus.com/tutorials/tools-and-tips/sublime-text-2-tips-and-tricks/\\\">http://net.tutsplus.com/tutorials/tools-and-tips/sublime-text-2-tips-and-tricks/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://net.tutsplus.com/tutorials/tools-and-tips/essential-textmate-shortcuts-tips-and-techniques/\\\">http://net.tutsplus.com/tutorials/tools-and-tips/essential-textmate-shortcuts-tips-and-techniques/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Remote debugging</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://developers.google.com/chrome/mobile/docs/debugging\\\">https://developers.google.com/chrome/mobile/docs/debugging</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Linting</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://www.jshint.com/\\\">http://www.jshint.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://developers.google.com/closure/utilities/\\\">https://developers.google.com/closure/utilities/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://code.google.com/p/closure-stylesheets/\\\">http://code.google.com/p/closure-stylesheets/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Testing</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://www.browserstack.com/\\\">http://www.browserstack.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://mogotest.com/\\\">http://mogotest.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://docs.jquery.com/QUnit\\\">http://docs.jquery.com/QUnit</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://pivotal.github.com/jasmine/\\\">http://pivotal.github.com/jasmine/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://code.google.com/p/js-test-driver/\\\">http://code.google.com/p/js-test-driver/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://testling.com/\\\">http://testling.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://seleniumhq.org/projects/\\\">http://seleniumhq.org/projects/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://watirwebdriver.com/\\\">http://watirwebdriver.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Deployment</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://developers.google.com/closure/compiler/\\\">https://developers.google.com/closure/compiler/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://developer.yahoo.com/yui/compressor/\\\">http://developer.yahoo.com/yui/compressor/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://code.google.com/p/htmlcompressor/\\\">http://code.google.com/p/htmlcompressor/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://www.codedread.com/scour/\\\">http://www.codedread.com/scour/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://imageoptim.com/\\\">http://imageoptim.com/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://optipng.sourceforge.net/\\\">http://optipng.sourceforge.net/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://trimage.org/\\\">http://trimage.org/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://pngquant.org/\\\">http://pngquant.org/</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://github.com/rflynn/imgmin\\\">https://github.com/rflynn/imgmin</a></p>\r\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">&nbsp;</p>','<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Last night I was visiting Paul Irishs blog and had a look at his excellent talk at jQuery UK 2012, TOOLING &amp; THE WEBAPP DEVELOPMENT STACK. It\\\'s an excellent &amp; fun talk and you should defiantly have a look at it. Paul talks about different Tools for frontend developers that can make you a lot esyer. Paul lists a ton of useful tools, and I tried to create a list of all of the tools he mentions as a nice, compact summary:</p>\n\n<p><p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Boilerplates</strong></p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">The HTML 5 Boilerplate, a good point to start on any HTML document</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://html5boilerplate.com/\\\">http://html5boilerplate.com/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">blueprint - the first css boilerplate, there a lot, lot more but you can&#92;\'t go wrong with blueprint</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://blueprintcss.org/\\\">http://blueprintcss.org/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Think IE 6 is hell? Try writing HTML in E-Mails. Luckly there are boilerplates too</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://htmlemailboilerplate.com/\\\">http://htmlemailboilerplate.com/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">The HTML 5 Boilerplate from the beginning, only optimized for mobile. Yay!</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://html5boilerplate.com/mobile\\\">http://html5boilerplate.com/mobile</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Writing Dojo? There&#92;\'s a boilerplate for it too, so you don&#92;\'t have to figure out the best practice</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://github.com/csnover/dojo-boilerplate\\\">https://github.com/csnover/dojo-boilerplate</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Or are you writing jQuery? Then there is a boilerplate for you, too!</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://jqueryboilerplate.com/\\\">http://jqueryboilerplate.com/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Styling</strong></p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Writing CSS can be a pain. SASS makes it easy again, with support of nested rules, variables, selector inheritance and more. Compiles down to normal, valid CSS 3</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://sass-lang.com/\\\">http://sass-lang.com/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Lala&nbsp; - need to have a look at this one myself</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://compass-style.org/\\\">http://compass-style.org/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Alternative to SASS, introduces variables, functions and nested rules to CSS</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://lesscss.org/\\\">http://lesscss.org/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Another SASS alternative, also introduces variables, functions conditionals mixings to CSS</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://code.google.com/p/closure-stylesheets/\\\">http://code.google.com/p/closure-stylesheets/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Sylus - also a SASS alternative</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://learnboost.github.com/stylus/\\\">http://learnboost.github.com/stylus/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Markup</strong></p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Haml. - A what ever for ruby. Looks nice</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://haml.info/\\\">http://haml.info/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Mardown - a simple Markuplanguage, used at github and stack overflow. also works in airpapr ;)</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/\\\">http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">A template engine for node.js - makes your HTML much simpler</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://jade-lang.com/\\\">http://jade-lang.com/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">DAFUQ</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://handlebarsjs.com/\\\">http://handlebarsjs.com/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Awesome tool to write html as fast as hell - really great</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://code.google.com/p/zen-coding/\\\">http://code.google.com/p/zen-coding/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Scripting</strong></p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">A list of languages that compile to JavaScript</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"https://github.com/jashkenas/coffee-script/wiki/List-of-languages-that-compile-to-JS\\\">https://github.com/jashkenas/coffee-script/wiki/List-of-languages-that-compile-to-JS</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">CoffeScript - a language that compiles directly to JavaScript - easy to use</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://coffeescript.org/\\\">http://coffeescript.org/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">Googls DART programming language - also compiles directly to JavaScript</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://www.dartlang.org/\\\">http://www.dartlang.org/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>ToDoMVC</strong></p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\">The Same ToDo app implemented in various different JavaScriptMV* frameworks - great if you want to compare different frameworks and see which one is best for you</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://addyosmani.github.com/todomvc/\\\">http://addyosmani.github.com/todomvc/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p2\\\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><strong>Tools</strong></p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://livereload.com/\\\">http://livereload.com/</a></p>\n<p class=\\\"p1\\\"><a href=\\\"http://incident57.com/codekit/\\\">http://incident5